        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:49PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Weesatche, or 10 miles north of Goliad, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Victoria, Goliad, Schroeder, Ander, Mission Valley, Weesatche, Weser,
Nursery, and Charco.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 183 between mile markers 628 and 640.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 580 and 582.
US Highway 87 between mile markers 798 and 800.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
